The Ministry of Social Welfare, Relief and Resettlement (Burmese: လူမှုဝန်ထမ်းကယ်ဆယ်ရေးနှင့်ပြန်လည် နေရာချထားရေး ဝန်ကြီးဌာန) administers Burma's social welfare, social relief and resettlement affairs.
The Ministry of Social Welfare, Relief and Resettlement is currently led by Win Myat Aye, who was appointed by President Htin Kyaw on 30 March 2016.
